# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# vocal-helper — local settings
#
# Copy this file to ``settings.yaml`` (which is git-ignored) and keep the
# ``engines.diarization_url`` below. The vocal-helper library reads it on
# import via ``vocal_helper._settings`` so the CLI, the example scripts and
# any library caller behave identically.
#
# The parser is hand-rolled (no PyYAML dependency) and only understands
# this flat two-level schema — keep new keys at the same indentation.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# REQUIRED — the self-hosted "diarization-engines" bundle. This single ZIP
# carries EVERY model weight the project needs (offline pyannote 3.1, NeMo
# Sortformer, the online pyannote/embedding embedder, and SpeechBrain
# VoxLingua107), so **no HuggingFace account or token is required** — the
# whole stack runs offline once the bundle is cached locally.
#
# How it is used: the URL is downloaded once, extracted and cached under
# ``~/.cache/vocal-helper``; later runs load straight from the cache.
# You may instead point this at a local directory holding the extracted
# bundle. A valid value looks like a ``https://…/diarization-engines.zip``
# URL or an absolute directory path.
#
# Resolution order (highest priority first):
#   1. ``$VH_DIARIZATION_ENGINES`` environment variable.
#   2. ``engines.diarization_url`` below.
#   3. The library's built-in default.
engines:
  diarization_url: https://deraison.ai/diarization-engines.zip
# That is the entire configuration. There is no HuggingFace token — the
# bundle carries every model weight the project needs.
